f\in L^{1}(\mathbb R)
\hat{f}(\xi)=\int_{\mathbb R} f(x)e^{-2\pi i \xi\cdot x} dx, (\xi \in \mathbb R);
f^{\vee}(x):=\hat{f}(-x)= \int_{\mathbb R} f(\xi) e^{2\pi i \xi\cdot x} d\xi, (x\in \mathbb R).
f\in L^{1}(\mathbb R)
\hat{f}\in L^{1}(\mathbb R)
(\hat{f})^{\vee}=f.
